# .gitignore for Meeting Summarizer
#
# WHY this file exists:
#   Git tracks changes to files. But some files should NEVER be committed:
#   - Secret keys (.env) — security risk
#   - Compiled/cached Python files (__pycache__) — generated, not source
#   - Virtual environment (venv/) — too large, platform-specific, reproducible via requirements.txt
#   - IDE config (.vscode/, .idea/) — personal preferences, not project code
#   - Output files (summaries/) — generated artifacts, not source code

# === SECRETS (CRITICAL — NEVER COMMIT) ===
.env
*.key
*.pem

# === PYTHON CACHE ===
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.pyc

# === VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT ===
venv/
.venv/
env/
ENV/

# === IDE CONFIG ===
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store

# === GENERATED OUTPUT ===
# Optionally ignore summaries (they're generated, not source code)
# Uncomment the next line if you don't want to track summaries in Git:
# summaries/

# === TRANSCRIPTS ===
# Transcripts may contain confidential information.
# Consider ignoring them if they contain sensitive meeting content:
# transcripts/
